title: Doll
creator: Philippines
description: Female fabric doll from the Philippines. Doll has dark beige skin and black hair, face painted on with detailed eyes, thick eyebrows, nostrils, and red lips. She wears a traditional Philippine costume, known as Filipiniana, or terno. It is characterized by "butterfly sleeves" which over-accentuate one's shoulders. The Filipiniana dress is made out of terracotta-colored (red-orange) lace with a skirt slit down the center. She wears yellow heeled slippers, which acts also as a mount to a square wooden base. The doll also wears faux pearl jewelry, such as a white necklace and droplet earrings. Her arms are able to bend with some inner wire construction, and one hand holds a fan, or pamaypay in Tagalog. Her hair is adorned with red-orange sequins.
subject: woman;dress
source: Philippine Collection, Burke Museum of Natural History and Culture, University of Washington
